    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model demonstrates adequate predictive capability for the relative hemolysis index across the full COU operating envelope. Discretization error (GCI 2.1%) and output comparison error (E_rms 0.043) are both within acceptance criteria. Six factors were appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. The evidence package supports acceptance of the computational model for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
